{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idc35dea79-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3112"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3112"},"text":"§ 3112.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Revolving fund loans","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The revolving fund established pursuant to part VII of Veterans Regulation Numbered 1(a) is continued in effect, and may be used by the Secretary, under regulations prescribed by the Secretary, for making advances, not in excess of twice the amount of the full-time institutional monthly subsistence allowance for a veteran with no dependents (as provided in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s3108/b"},"text":"section 3108(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":") to veterans pursuing rehabilitation programs under this chapter. Such advances, and advances from such fund made before the effective date of the Veterans’ Rehabilitation and Education Amendments of 1980, shall bear no interest and shall be repaid in such installments, as may be determined by the Secretary, by proper deductions from future payments of compensation, pension, subsistence allowance, educational assistance allowance, or retirement pay."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idc35dea7a-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/466/tI/s101/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–466, title I, § 101(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/2181"},"text":"94 Stat. 2181","children":[],"tail":", § 1512; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/237/tIV/s423/b/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–237, title IV, § 423(b)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 1989","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/103/2092"},"text":"103 Stat. 2092","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 3112 and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/83/s5/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–83, § 5(a)","children":[],"tail":", (c)(1), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-08-06"},"text":"Aug. 6, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/406"},"text":"105 Stat. 406","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idc35dea7b-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idc35dea7c-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idc35dea7d-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The revolving fund established pursuant to part VII of Veterans Regulation Numbered 1(a), referred to in text, means the vocational rehabilitation revolving fund established by par. 8 of part VII of Veterans Regulation Numbered 1(a), as added by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1943-03-24/ch22/s2"},"text":"act Mar. 24, 1943, ch. 22, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/57/44"},"text":"57 Stat. 44","children":[],"tail":", which was set out in chapter 12A of former Title 38, Pensions, Bonuses, and Veterans’ Relief. The appropriation for such fund made by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1943-07-12/ch218/s1"},"text":"act July 12, 1943, ch. 218, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/57/434"},"text":"57 Stat. 434","children":[],"tail":", was reduced by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-06-24/ch359/tI/s101/part"},"text":"act June 24, 1954, ch. 359, title I, § 101(part)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68/293"},"text":"68 Stat. 293","children":[],"tail":", and repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/857/s14/82"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–857, § 14(82)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-09-02"},"text":"Sept. 2, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/1272"},"text":"72 Stat. 1272","children":[],"tail":". Part VII of Veterans Regulation Numbered 1(a) was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/857/s14/67"},"text":"section 14(67) of Pub. L. 85–857","children":[],"tail":", effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1959-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 1959","children":[],"tail":", which provided in part, that repeal of part VII should not take effect in such manner as to impair the operation of the deferred repeal of a portion of paragraph 9 of the part as provided in section 21 of the Government Employees Training Act, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/507"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–507","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-07-07"},"text":"July 7, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/337"},"text":"72 Stat. 337","children":[],"tail":". For continuation of certain rights and benefits see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/857/s12"},"text":"section 12 of Pub. L. 85–857","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note preceding part I of this title."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For effective date of the Veterans’ Rehabilitation and Education Amendments of 1980, referred to in text, see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/466/s802"},"text":"section 802 of Pub. L. 96–466","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s3100"},"text":"section 3100 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idc35dea7e-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Prior section 3112 was renumbered ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s5312"},"text":"section 5312 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Provisions similar to those comprising this section were contained in former ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s1507"},"text":"section 1507 of this title","children":[],"tail":" prior to the general revision of this chapter by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/466"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–466","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idc35dea7f-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1991—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/83"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–83","children":[],"tail":" renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s1512"},"text":"section 1512 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section and substituted “3108(b)” for “1508(b)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1989—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/237"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–237","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Secretary” for “Administrator” wherever appearing."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idc35dea80-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail"